name: Ramin Firoozye
bio: Have developed many mobile apps that have front-paged and charted. Apps have won a number of awards including iOSDevCamp and Macworld Best of Show.
column17: Have developed many mobile apps that have front-paged and charted. Apps have won a number of awards including iOSDevCamp and Macworld Best of Show.
column31:
- Put together a team to develop a multimedia browser -- competing against Netscape and Macromedia products. Company was acquired by Microsoft. 

- Wrote one of the first digital video streaming servers. Put together an NIST proposal for a standard for streaming digital video (lost to NBC).

- Built a prototype for the first Digital Public Library for NASA.

- Independently developed a browser add-on product that added local database support. Shipped over 100M copies. 

- First self-published mobile app won Macworld Best of Show and is in operation in over 80 countries. 

- Have developed several mobile apps for clients that have front-paged and charted.

- Worked on commercial wearable projects with support for both Bluetooth LE and Classic Bluetooth/MFI. 

- Actively working on a next-generation browser for developing native mobile apps, a universal Bluetooth LE  API, and an infrastructure for iBeacon. The goal is to support dynamic mobile interfaces for devices. Work in progress.
column33:
Mainly interested in consulting work helping folks build their mobile apps and get to market fast.

Very much interested in the intersection of iOS/Android and physical devices via Bluetooth Low-Energy, classic Bluetooth, Wifi, and iBeacon.
